<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/jquery@3.3.1/dist/jquery.min.js"></script>
    <script src="/homepage.js" defer></script>
    <link
      rel="stylesheet"
      type="text/css"
      href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/fomantic-ui@2.8.7/dist/semantic.min.css"
    />
    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/fomantic-ui@2.8.7/dist/semantic.min.js"></script>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles/index.css" />
    <title>Disparty-peer to peer video streaming service</title>
  </head>

  <body>
    <header style="padding-top: 10px" class="ui huge center aligned header">
      <h1 style="font-size: 200%">DISPARTY</h1>
    </header>
    <div class="container">
      <%- include ('partials/chat.ejs') %>
      <div class="ui padded row placeholder container segment">
        <form class="ui form" id="join-form" action="/join-room">
          <div class="ui center aligned container">
            <h2 style="margin: 30px 0" class="ui center aligned header">
              â€‚First enter your nickname
            </h2>
            <div class="ui input">
              <input
                id="nickname"
                required
                type="text"
                minlength="3"
                oninvalid="validateField(this)"
                placeholder="nickname"
              />
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="ui center aligned container">
            <h2 style="margin: 30px 0" class="ui center aligned header">
              And then choose to join an existing room or create a new one
            </h2>
          </div>
          <div class="ui two column stackable center aligned grid">
            <div class="middle aligned row">
              <div class="column">
                <div class="ui icon header">
                  <i class="door open icon"></i>
                  Join existing room
                </div>
                <div class="field">
                  <div class="ui action input">
                    <input
                      type="text"
                      minlength="4"
                      name="room-id"
                      id="room-id"
                      oninvalid="validateField(this)"
                      placeholder="Enter room Id"
                    />
                    <button
                      class="ui icon button"
                      type="button"
                      id="paste-button"
                    >
                      <i class="paste icon"></i>
                    </button>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="field">
                  <button
                    id="join-room-btn"
                    type="submit"
                    form="join-form"
                    class="ui primary button"
                    onclick="makeRoomIdRequired()"
                  >
                    Join room
                  </button>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="column">
                <div class="ui icon header">
                  <i class="plus circle icon"></i>
                  Create a new room
                </div>
                <div class="field">
                  <button
                    formaction="/new-room"
                    style="width: fit-content"
                    class="ui primary button"
                    onclick="makeRoomIdNotRequired()"
                  >
                    Create
                  </button>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </form>
      </div>
      <div class="ui container">
        <div class="ui segments">
          <h2 class="ui top attached header">What is disparty?</h2>
          <div class="ui attached segment">
            <p>
              Disparty is a decentralized, peer to peer communication platform.
              It offers chat, webcam streaming and streaming of local video so
              friends and family can watch a movie together remotely.
            </p>
          </div>
          <h2 class="ui attached header">Why is disparty?</h2>
          <div class="ui attached segment">
            <p>For three reasons:</p>
            <div class="ui bulleted list">
              <div class="item">
                <div class="header">Private and secure.</div>
                <div class="description">
                  Disparty, unlike competitive solutions does not rely on a
                  server to route video streams, as these are streamed directly
                  from peer to peer. There is only a very small server used to
                  establish the connection between individual peers.
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="item">
                <div class="header">Completely open source.</div>
                <div class="description">
                  Don't trust us with the security? Visit
                  <a href="https://github.com/adik6555/disparty"
                    >our github repo</a
                  >
                  and see for yourself.
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="item">
                <div class="header">We had to.</div>
                <div class="description">
                  Disparty was done as an educational project for a university
                  course.
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <h2 class="ui attached header">How is disparty?</h2>
          <div class="ui attached segment">
            <div class="ui bulleted list">
              <div class="item">
                Basically vanilla webdev package with
                <a href="https://jquery.com/">jQuery</a>.
              </div>
              <div class="item">
                <a href="https://fomantic-ui.com/">Fomantic-UI</a> for this
                <em data-emoji=":fire:"></em> UI.
              </div>

              <div class="item">
                <a href="https://github.com/feross/simple-peer/">Simple-peer</a>
                to handle all the p2p streaming magic.
              </div>

              <div class="item">
                <a href="https://nodejs.org/en/">NodeJs</a> and
                <a href="https://expressjs.com/">ExpressJs</a> as a signalling
                server.
              </div>

              <div class="item">
                And lastly..substantial amount of cheap brainpower to put this
                all together.
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <h2 class="ui attached header">Where is disparty?</h2>
          <div class="ui attached segment">
            <p>
              <a href="https://github.com/adik6555/disparty">Here.</a>
            </p>
          </div>
          <h2 class="ui attached header">Who is disparty?</h2>
          <div class="ui attached segment">
            <p>
              Two guys. Used to be three, third one dropped out.<em
                data-emoji=":cry:"
              ></em
              ><br />
              Namely:
            </p>
            <div class="ui bulleted list">
              <div class="item">
                <p><a href="https://github.com/adik6555">Adam Petro</a></p>
              </div>
              <div class="item">
                <p>
                  <a href="https://github.com/j-krzyz">Jakub Jan Krzyzynski</a>
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
